qas.question: When did the Spanish arrive to America?

answers.text: Spanish arrived in the territory of the modern United States with Ponce de León in 1513.

qas.question: Did Europeans speak Spanish in America?

answers.text: Spanish was the language spoken by the first permanent European settlers in North America.

qas.question: Where is the oldest settlement in America?
What is the oldest city of the United States territory?

answers.text: The oldest city in all of the U.S. territory, as of 1898, is San Juan, capital of Puerto Rico
